The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at a naturalization ceremony for new American citizens. He congratulated the individuals on becoming citizens and welcomed them to the White House and the American family. Pence emphasized that America is a generous and welcoming nation of immigrants, and encouraged the new citizens to study and understand the Constitution, as well as the rights and liberties that come with citizenship. He reminded them of the sacrifices made by previous generations and urged them to give back to their communities and contribute to the nation. Pence concluded by telling the new citizens to have faith, dream big, and work hard, as America offers unlimited possibilities for success.